item.content:
&lt;div class=&quot;col-lg-5&quot;&gt;
	&lt;p&gt;Our customer had just recently had a large extension project completed on their house and were looking for a new look to their garden&lt;/p&gt;
	&lt;p&gt;We got together to discuss their plans and come up with some initial ideas, the aim was to create a garden that provided a flat area for entreating and for the kids to play in, with a small circular seating area feature, a path and steps... all to try and fit in with the original features of the property as much as possible using materials that will be more durable and less likely to wear and discolour over time unlike some manufactured alternatives might do.&lt;/p&gt;
	&lt;p&gt;Our solution was to base all the stonework on real, natural sandstone (paving is natural sandstone), gravel from a local quarry and new turf for the lawn area.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
